* `2over` duplicates the top element on the stack twice. Since there were three elements on the stack before, it duplicates each of those elements once, resulting in six copies of 17 on the stack. The new stack is now 17 17 17 9 10 6.
* `2dup` duplicates the entire stack twice. This results in four copies of the original stack, for a total of sixteen elements on the stack. The final stack is as shown above.
